commitResults.messageTitle: Add Parser and SortCommand to support sorting
commitResults.messageBody:
Lack of Parser and SortCommand files to support sorting

Added a SortCommandParser class to parse parameters
passed for sort command. Sort command utilizes prefixes
f/ and o/ for field and order respectively.

Added a SortCommand class. SortCommand object contains
field and object attributes to denote the specific
field and object to be implemented.

Implementation will be done in the next commit.

Codecov was not passing due to lack of Tests

Added tests for SortCommandParser class.

NOTE: userInput for Tests contain an initial whitespace
due to how ArgumentTokenizer class creates tokens.

More details can be seen in findPrefixPosition() method
in ArgumentTokenizer class where it searches for
indexOf() with a whitespace.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add More tests to improve code coverage
commitResults.messageBody:
Codecov was failing due to lack of tests

Added more tests to improve code coverage.

Tests added include tests for SortCommand and
AddressBookParser
Add CommandHistory Class and corresponding basic test cases + DG Modifications

Modified the address book to be able to sort contacts
Contacts can be sorted in ascending or descending order
based on name or tags

When sorting based on tags, it will sort the tags
for each contact, and take the first tag to be
compared.

Issues arised due to unused imports

Removed the unused imports in order to pass CI

CI was not passing due to lack of code coverage

Added tests to cover execute() for SortCommand
Tests include positive and negative tests for all
current fields and ordering supported.

SortCommand did not support Case Insensitivity for field and order

SortCommand now supports Case Insensitivity, field and order
and converted to lowercase when running execute()

Filter command can be used to filter contacts based
on one or more tags.

Tags are checked for edge cases but checks may not be
exhaustive.

Tests will be added in the next commit.

Added tests pertaining to the following classes:
* FilterCommand
* FilterCommandParser
* TagsContainsTagPredicate
